There is no notion of &quot;lines&quot; in the c++ language. If you like you can put all your code on a single line (not recommended). If you write

    int main() {
        ;     // &lt;--
    }

Then in the line marked with the comment you have an empty statement that does nothing. See also [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7479946/whats-an-expression-and-expression-statement-in-c). The quesiton is about statements vs expressions, but it might also help to better understand your issue.

